 East London - Buffalo City Metro Law Enforcement officers arrested brewers and confiscated illegal home-brewed liquor and traditional beer in iZinyoka near King Williams Town on Wednesday. "The City would like to send a stern warning to those who are brewing and selling liquor, we are taking the rules and regulations of this lockdown seriously and we will arrest those who do not abide by these rules;" said BCM spokesperson, Samkelo Ngwenya. Brewing, selling alcohol for consumption is prohibited under COVID-19 Level 4 restrictions. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 